{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LqCrFAeC5TM1G8mgQJxKzs","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a final summary document based on all the files I've read:\n\n## Project Structure Report for F31 Implementation\n\n### Project Overview\n- **Framework**: Next.js 16 with React 19\n- **Testing**: Vitest with React Testing Library (jsdom environment)\n- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS + MUI Material\n- **Build Tools**: TypeScript, Biome for linting\n- **Database**: ClickHouse\n\n---\n\n### 1. **package.json** — Commands and Dependencies\n\n**Test/Build/Lint Commands:**\n```\nnpm run dev          - Run with ClickHouse and Next.js concurrently\nnpm run build        - Next.js build\nnpm run start        - Start production server\nnpm run test         - vitest run\nnpm run lint         - biome check\nnpm run lint:fix     - biome check --fix\nnpm run typecheck    - tsc --noEmit\nnpm run migrate      - tsx scripts/migrate.ts\n```\n\n**Key Dependencies:**\n- React 19.2.4 + React DOM 19.2.4\n- Next 16.2.3\n- @mui/material ^9.0.0\n- @emotion/react, @emotion/styled (styling)\n- recharts ^3.8.1 (charting)\n- @testing-library/react ^16.3.2\n- vitest ^4.1.4\n- jsdom ^29.0.2 (test environment)\n\n---\n\n### 2. **vitest.config.ts** — Test Configuration\n\nLocated at: `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/vitest.config.ts`\n\n```typescript\n- Environment: \"node\" (default)\n- Path alias: \"@\" → src\n- Excludes: playwright_tests/**/*.spec.ts\n- For jsdom tests: Use `// @vitest-environment jsdom` at top of file\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Test File Conventions**\n\n**Location Pattern:**\n- Component tests go in `src/components/<module>/__tests__/<ComponentName>.test.tsx`\n- Hook tests go in `src/components/<module>/__tests__/<hookName>.test.ts`\n\n**File Examples:**\n- `/src/components/ui/__tests__/JsonChip.test.tsx`\n- `/src/components/test/__tests__/CustomEventForm.test.tsx`\n- `/src/components/trends/__tests__/useTrends.test.ts`\n\n**Test File Structure Pattern:**\n```typescript\n// @vitest-environment jsdom (for component tests)\nimport { cleanup, render, screen, fireEvent, waitFor } from \"@testing-library/react\";\nimport { afterEach, beforeEach, describe, expect, it, vi } from \"vitest\";\nimport { ComponentUnderTest } from \"@/components/path/ComponentUnderTest\";\n\nafterEach(() => {\n  cleanup();\n  vi.clearAllMocks();\n});\n\ndescribe(\"ComponentName\", () => {\n  describe(\"feature area 1\", () => {\n    it(\"does something specific\", () => {\n      // test code\n    });\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Hook Testing Pattern** (no jsdom directive):\n```typescript\nimport { act, renderHook, waitFor } from \"@testing-library/react\";\nimport { beforeEach, afterEach, describe, expect, it, vi } from \"vitest\";\n\nconst mockFetch = vi.fn();\n\nbeforeEach(() => {\n  vi.stubGlobal(\"fetch\", mockFetch);\n});\n\nafterEach(() => {\n  vi.clearAllMocks();\n  vi.unstubAllGlobals();\n});\n\ndescribe(\"useHookName\", () => {\n  it(\"does something\", async () => {\n    const { result } = renderHook(() => useHookName());\n    // assertions\n  });\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **src/lib/generator.ts** — Core Types and Interfaces\n\n**File Location:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/lib/generator.ts`\n\n**Key Types:**\n```typescript\nexport type JobStatus = \"queued\" | \"running\" | \"complete\" | \"failed\" | \"cancelled\";\nexport type NumericVariance = \"low\" | \"medium\" | \"high\";\n\nexport interface EventTypeWeight {\n  name: string;\n  weight: number;\n}\n\nexport interface JobConfig {\n  total: number;\n  users: number;\n  start: string;\n  end: string;\n  event_types: EventTypeWeight[];\n  identity_resolution: boolean;\n  anonymous_ratio: number;\n  numeric_variance: NumericVariance;\n}\n\nexport interface JobConfigInput {\n  total?: number;\n  users?: number;\n  start?: string;\n  end?: string;\n  event_types?: EventTypeWeight[];\n  identity_resolution?: boolean;\n  anonymous_ratio?: number;\n  numeric_variance?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface JobState {\n  job_id: string;\n  status: JobStatus;\n  inserted: number;\n  total: number;\n  throughput: number;\n  eta_seconds: number;\n  elapsed_ms: number;\n  error?: string;\n  config: JobConfig;\n  cancelled: boolean;\n  created_at: number;\n}\n```\n\n**Default Event Types:**\n- \"Page Viewed\" (weight: 0.4)\n- \"Button Clicked\" (weight: 0.15)\n- \"Signup Completed\" (weight: 0.12)\n- \"Purchase Completed\" (weight: 0.13)\n- \"Subscription Renewed\" (weight: 0.12)\n- \"Support Ticket Opened\" (weight: 0.08)\n\n**Public API Functions:**\n```typescript\nexport function startGenerationJob(input: JobConfigInput): string\nexport function getJob(id: string): JobState | undefined\nexport function cancelJob(id: string): boolean\nexport function listJobs(): JobState[]\nexport function _clearJobs(): void  // for testing only\nexport function generateBatchEvents(\n  config: JobConfig,\n  users: GeneratedUser[],\n  startDate: Date,\n  endDate: Date,\n  rand: () => number,\n  batchSize: number,\n): GeneratedEvent[]\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. **src/app/generate/page.tsx** — Current Placeholder\n\n**File Location:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/app/generate/page.tsx`\n\n**Current Content (minimal):**\n```typescript\nimport Typography from \"@mui/material/Typography\";\n\nexport default function GeneratePage(): React.JSX.Element {\n  return (\n    <Typography variant=\"h4\" component=\"h1\">\n      Generate\n    </Typography>\n  );\n}\n```\n\nThis is where you'll integrate the GeneratePanel component.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **API Routes**\n\n#### **POST /api/generate/start** \n`/src/app/api/generate/start/route.ts`\n\n```typescript\n- Accepts: JobConfigInput JSON body\n- Returns: { job_id: string } (status 201) on success\n- Returns: { error: string } (status 400) on validation error\n- Throws synchronously if config invalid\n- Calls: startGenerationJob(body)\n```\n\n#### **GET /api/generate/[job_id]/status** \n`/src/app/api/generate/[job_id]/status/route.ts`\n\n```typescript\n- Server-Sent Events (SSE) streaming\n- Polls every 500ms from in-memory job store\n- Returns: { status, inserted, total, throughput, eta_seconds } (for running)\n- Returns: { status, inserted, total, elapsed_ms } (for complete)\n- Terminal statuses: \"complete\", \"failed\", \"cancelled\"\n- Closes stream after terminal status\n- Returns: { error: \"Job not found.\" } (status 404) if job_id not found\n```\n\n#### **POST /api/generate/[job_id]/cancel**\n`/src/app/api/generate/[job_id]/cancel/route.ts`\n\n```typescript\n- Sets cancellation flag on job\n- Returns: { cancelled: true } (status 200) on success\n- Returns: { error: \"Job not found.\" } (status 404) if job_id not found\n- Generation loop checks flag between batches\n```\n\n#### **GET /api/generate/jobs**\n`/src/app/api/generate/jobs/route.ts`\n\n```typescript\n- Returns: JobState[] (all jobs in memory)\n- Simple listing without filtering\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. **src/app/layout.tsx** — App Shell Structure\n\n**File Location:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/app/layout.tsx`\n\n```typescript\n- Layout with MUI AppRouterCacheProvider\n- Left sidebar: <Sidebar /> component\n- Main content area: <main className=\"flex-1 p-6\">{children}</main>\n- Fonts: Geist Sans and Mono from Google Fonts\n- Tailwind with h-full, min-h-full, antialiased classes\n```\n\nThe `/generate` page content will render inside the `<main>` area.\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Component Structure Pattern**\n\nBased on `/src/components/test/` folder, the pattern is:\n\n```\nsrc/components/generate/\n├── GeneratePanel.tsx           (main component)\n├── GenerateForm.tsx            (form subcomponent)\n├── GenerateProgress.tsx        (progress display)\n├── useGenerateJob.ts           (custom hook for API calls)\n└── __tests__/\n    ├── GeneratePanel.test.tsx\n    ├── GenerateForm.test.tsx\n    ├── GenerateProgress.test.tsx\n    └── useGenerateJob.test.ts\n```\n\n**No `src/components/generate/` folder exists yet** — you'll create it.\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Test Examples Overview**\n\n**Component Test Example** (`JsonChip.test.tsx`):\n- Uses `@testing-library/react` render, screen, fireEvent\n- Tests render states, interactions, expansions\n- Cleanup and mock clearing in afterEach\n- Organized with nested describe blocks\n\n**Hook Test Example** (`useEventSender.test.ts`):\n- Uses `renderHook` from testing library\n- Mocks `fetch` globally with `vi.stubGlobal`\n- Uses `act()` and `waitFor()` for async operations\n- Tests initial state, API calls, side effects\n\n**Form Component Test** (`CustomEventForm.test.tsx`):\n- Tests collapsed/expanded states\n- Form submission with mocked handlers\n- Input validation and error feedback\n- User interaction patterns (fireEvent.click, fireEvent.change)\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Key Testing Patterns Used in Project**\n\n1. **Setup/Teardown:**\n   ```typescript\n   beforeEach(() => { /* setup */ });\n   afterEach(() => { cleanup(); vi.clearAllMocks(); });\n   ```\n\n2. **Mocking fetch:**\n   ```typescript\n   const mockFetch = vi.fn();\n   beforeEach(() => vi.stubGlobal(\"fetch\", mockFetch));\n   afterEach(() => vi.unstubAllGlobals());\n   ```\n\n3. **Async hook testing:**\n   ```typescript\n   await act(async () => {\n     await result.current.someAsyncMethod();\n   });\n   ```\n\n4. **Waiting for updates:**\n   ```typescript\n   await waitFor(() => expect(result.current.loading).toBe(false));\n   ```\n\n5. **Testing rendered output:**\n   ```typescript\n   const button = screen.getByRole(\"button\", { name: /button text/i });\n   expect(button).toHaveProperty(\"disabled\", false);\n   ```\n\n---\n\n### 11. **Summary for F31 Implementation**\n\nYou need to create:\n1. **Custom hook** (`useGenerateJob.ts`) to handle:\n   - POST /api/generate/start\n   - GET /api/generate/[job_id]/status (SSE streaming)\n   - POST /api/generate/[job_id]/cancel\n   - GET /api/generate/jobs\n\n2. **Form component** (`GenerateForm.tsx`) to accept JobConfigInput fields\n\n3. **Progress display** (`GenerateProgress.tsx`) to show live metrics\n\n4. **Main panel** (`GeneratePanel.tsx`) orchestrating form, progress, and controls\n\n5. **Tests** in `__tests__/` folder following the established patterns\n\nAll should be in `/src/components/generate/` with tests in `/src/components/generate/__tests__/`"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e2b9e14-c306-4c04-b64f-1d0d531c58b6","uuid":"d3ec44be-ef56-4bde-bdee-b8b19f33d6c4","timestamp":"2026-04-15T18:39:50.355Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the project structure to implement F31. Please explore the following and report back:\n\n1. Read `package.json` for test/lint/build commands and dependencies\n2. Read `vitest.config.*` or any test config files\n3. Read a few existing test files to understand conventions (look in `src/components/` or similar)\n4. Read `src/lib/generator.ts` — types used by the generator\n5. Read `src/app/generate/page.tsx` — current placeholder\n6. Read `src/app/api/generate/start/route.ts` — the start API\n7. Read `src/app/api/generate/[job_id]/status/route.ts` — SSE status API\n8. Read `src/app/api/generate/[job_id]/cancel/route.ts`\n9. Read `src/app/api/generate/jobs/route.ts`\n10. Read an existing component test file like `src/components/test/` folder tests if they exist\n11. Check if there's a `src/components/generate/` folder already\n12. Read `src/app/layout.tsx` to understand navigation/shell\n\nReport the full contents of each file and any relevant context about how tests are structured in this project.","agentId":"ac8d391b65abbf1f8","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a final summary document based on all the files I've read:\n\n## Project Structure Report for F31 Implementation\n\n### Project Overview\n- **Framework**: Next.js 16 with React 19\n- **Testing**: Vitest with React Testing Library (jsdom environment)\n- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS + MUI Material\n- **Build Tools**: TypeScript, Biome for linting\n- **Database**: ClickHouse\n\n---\n\n### 1. **package.json** — Commands and Dependencies\n\n**Test/Build/Lint Commands:**\n```\nnpm run dev          - Run with ClickHouse and Next.js concurrently\nnpm run build        - Next.js build\nnpm run start        - Start production server\nnpm run test         - vitest run\nnpm run lint         - biome check\nnpm run lint:fix     - biome check --fix\nnpm run typecheck    - tsc --noEmit\nnpm run migrate      - tsx scripts/migrate.ts\n```\n\n**Key Dependencies:**\n- React 19.2.4 + React DOM 19.2.4\n- Next 16.2.3\n- @mui/material ^9.0.0\n- @emotion/react, @emotion/styled (styling)\n- recharts ^3.8.1 (charting)\n- @testing-library/react ^16.3.2\n- vitest ^4.1.4\n- jsdom ^29.0.2 (test environment)\n\n---\n\n### 2. **vitest.config.ts** — Test Configuration\n\nLocated at: `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/vitest.config.ts`\n\n```typescript\n- Environment: \"node\" (default)\n- Path alias: \"@\" → src\n- Excludes: playwright_tests/**/*.spec.ts\n- For jsdom tests: Use `// @vitest-environment jsdom` at top of file\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Test File Conventions**\n\n**Location Pattern:**\n- Component tests go in `src/components/<module>/__tests__/<ComponentName>.test.tsx`\n- Hook tests go in `src/components/<module>/__tests__/<hookName>.test.ts`\n\n**File Examples:**\n- `/src/components/ui/__tests__/JsonChip.test.tsx`\n- `/src/components/test/__tests__/CustomEventForm.test.tsx`\n- `/src/components/trends/__tests__/useTrends.test.ts`\n\n**Test File Structure Pattern:**\n```typescript\n// @vitest-environment jsdom (for component tests)\nimport { cleanup, render, screen, fireEvent, waitFor } from \"@testing-library/react\";\nimport { afterEach, beforeEach, describe, expect, it, vi } from \"vitest\";\nimport { ComponentUnderTest } from \"@/components/path/ComponentUnderTest\";\n\nafterEach(() => {\n  cleanup();\n  vi.clearAllMocks();\n});\n\ndescribe(\"ComponentName\", () => {\n  describe(\"feature area 1\", () => {\n    it(\"does something specific\", () => {\n      // test code\n    });\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Hook Testing Pattern** (no jsdom directive):\n```typescript\nimport { act, renderHook, waitFor } from \"@testing-library/react\";\nimport { beforeEach, afterEach, describe, expect, it, vi } from \"vitest\";\n\nconst mockFetch = vi.fn();\n\nbeforeEach(() => {\n  vi.stubGlobal(\"fetch\", mockFetch);\n});\n\nafterEach(() => {\n  vi.clearAllMocks();\n  vi.unstubAllGlobals();\n});\n\ndescribe(\"useHookName\", () => {\n  it(\"does something\", async () => {\n    const { result } = renderHook(() => useHookName());\n    // assertions\n  });\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **src/lib/generator.ts** — Core Types and Interfaces\n\n**File Location:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/lib/generator.ts`\n\n**Key Types:**\n```typescript\nexport type JobStatus = \"queued\" | \"running\" | \"complete\" | \"failed\" | \"cancelled\";\nexport type NumericVariance = \"low\" | \"medium\" | \"high\";\n\nexport interface EventTypeWeight {\n  name: string;\n  weight: number;\n}\n\nexport interface JobConfig {\n  total: number;\n  users: number;\n  start: string;\n  end: string;\n  event_types: EventTypeWeight[];\n  identity_resolution: boolean;\n  anonymous_ratio: number;\n  numeric_variance: NumericVariance;\n}\n\nexport interface JobConfigInput {\n  total?: number;\n  users?: number;\n  start?: string;\n  end?: string;\n  event_types?: EventTypeWeight[];\n  identity_resolution?: boolean;\n  anonymous_ratio?: number;\n  numeric_variance?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface JobState {\n  job_id: string;\n  status: JobStatus;\n  inserted: number;\n  total: number;\n  throughput: number;\n  eta_seconds: number;\n  elapsed_ms: number;\n  error?: string;\n  config: JobConfig;\n  cancelled: boolean;\n  created_at: number;\n}\n```\n\n**Default Event Types:**\n- \"Page Viewed\" (weight: 0.4)\n- \"Button Clicked\" (weight: 0.15)\n- \"Signup Completed\" (weight: 0.12)\n- \"Purchase Completed\" (weight: 0.13)\n- \"Subscription Renewed\" (weight: 0.12)\n- \"Support Ticket Opened\" (weight: 0.08)\n\n**Public API Functions:**\n```typescript\nexport function startGenerationJob(input: JobConfigInput): string\nexport function getJob(id: string): JobState | undefined\nexport function cancelJob(id: string): boolean\nexport function listJobs(): JobState[]\nexport function _clearJobs(): void  // for testing only\nexport function generateBatchEvents(\n  config: JobConfig,\n  users: GeneratedUser[],\n  startDate: Date,\n  endDate: Date,\n  rand: () => number,\n  batchSize: number,\n): GeneratedEvent[]\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. **src/app/generate/page.tsx** — Current Placeholder\n\n**File Location:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/app/generate/page.tsx`\n\n**Current Content (minimal):**\n```typescript\nimport Typography from \"@mui/material/Typography\";\n\nexport default function GeneratePage(): React.JSX.Element {\n  return (\n    <Typography variant=\"h4\" component=\"h1\">\n      Generate\n    </Typography>\n  );\n}\n```\n\nThis is where you'll integrate the GeneratePanel component.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **API Routes**\n\n#### **POST /api/generate/start** \n`/src/app/api/generate/start/route.ts`\n\n```typescript\n- Accepts: JobConfigInput JSON body\n- Returns: { job_id: string } (status 201) on success\n- Returns: { error: string } (status 400) on validation error\n- Throws synchronously if config invalid\n- Calls: startGenerationJob(body)\n```\n\n#### **GET /api/generate/[job_id]/status** \n`/src/app/api/generate/[job_id]/status/route.ts`\n\n```typescript\n- Server-Sent Events (SSE) streaming\n- Polls every 500ms from in-memory job store\n- Returns: { status, inserted, total, throughput, eta_seconds } (for running)\n- Returns: { status, inserted, total, elapsed_ms } (for complete)\n- Terminal statuses: \"complete\", \"failed\", \"cancelled\"\n- Closes stream after terminal status\n- Returns: { error: \"Job not found.\" } (status 404) if job_id not found\n```\n\n#### **POST /api/generate/[job_id]/cancel**\n`/src/app/api/generate/[job_id]/cancel/route.ts`\n\n```typescript\n- Sets cancellation flag on job\n- Returns: { cancelled: true } (status 200) on success\n- Returns: { error: \"Job not found.\" } (status 404) if job_id not found\n- Generation loop checks flag between batches\n```\n\n#### **GET /api/generate/jobs**\n`/src/app/api/generate/jobs/route.ts`\n\n```typescript\n- Returns: JobState[] (all jobs in memory)\n- Simple listing without filtering\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. **src/app/layout.tsx** — App Shell Structure\n\n**File Location:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/app/layout.tsx`\n\n```typescript\n- Layout with MUI AppRouterCacheProvider\n- Left sidebar: <Sidebar /> component\n- Main content area: <main className=\"flex-1 p-6\">{children}</main>\n- Fonts: Geist Sans and Mono from Google Fonts\n- Tailwind with h-full, min-h-full, antialiased classes\n```\n\nThe `/generate` page content will render inside the `<main>` area.\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Component Structure Pattern**\n\nBased on `/src/components/test/` folder, the pattern is:\n\n```\nsrc/components/generate/\n├── GeneratePanel.tsx           (main component)\n├── GenerateForm.tsx            (form subcomponent)\n├── GenerateProgress.tsx        (progress display)\n├── useGenerateJob.ts           (custom hook for API calls)\n└── __tests__/\n    ├── GeneratePanel.test.tsx\n    ├── GenerateForm.test.tsx\n    ├── GenerateProgress.test.tsx\n    └── useGenerateJob.test.ts\n```\n\n**No `src/components/generate/` folder exists yet** — you'll create it.\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Test Examples Overview**\n\n**Component Test Example** (`JsonChip.test.tsx`):\n- Uses `@testing-library/react` render, screen, fireEvent\n- Tests render states, interactions, expansions\n- Cleanup and mock clearing in afterEach\n- Organized with nested describe blocks\n\n**Hook Test Example** (`useEventSender.test.ts`):\n- Uses `renderHook` from testing library\n- Mocks `fetch` globally with `vi.stubGlobal`\n- Uses `act()` and `waitFor()` for async operations\n- Tests initial state, API calls, side effects\n\n**Form Component Test** (`CustomEventForm.test.tsx`):\n- Tests collapsed/expanded states\n- Form submission with mocked handlers\n- Input validation and error feedback\n- User interaction patterns (fireEvent.click, fireEvent.change)\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Key Testing Patterns Used in Project**\n\n1. **Setup/Teardown:**\n   ```typescript\n   beforeEach(() => { /* setup */ });\n   afterEach(() => { cleanup(); vi.clearAllMocks(); });\n   ```\n\n2. **Mocking fetch:**\n   ```typescript\n   const mockFetch = vi.fn();\n   beforeEach(() => vi.stubGlobal(\"fetch\", mockFetch));\n   afterEach(() => vi.unstubAllGlobals());\n   ```\n\n3. **Async hook testing:**\n   ```typescript\n   await act(async () => {\n     await result.current.someAsyncMethod();\n   });\n   ```\n\n4. **Waiting for updates:**\n   ```typescript\n   await waitFor(() => expect(result.current.loading).toBe(false));\n   ```\n\n5. **Testing rendered output:**\n   ```typescript\n   const button = screen.getByRole(\"button\", { name: /button text/i });\n   expect(button).toHaveProperty(\"disabled\", false);\n   ```\n\n---\n\n### 11. **Summary for F31 Implementation**\n\nYou need to create:\n1. **Custom hook** (`useGenerateJob.ts`) to handle:\n   - POST /api/generate/start\n   - GET /api/generate/[job_id]/status (SSE streaming)\n   - POST /api/generate/[job_id]/cancel\n   - GET /api/generate/jobs\n\n2. **Form component** (`GenerateForm.tsx`) to accept JobConfigInput fields\n\n3. **Progress display** (`GenerateProgress.tsx`) to show live metrics\n\n4. **Main panel** (`GeneratePanel.tsx`) orchestrating form, progress, and controls\n\n5. **Tests** in `__tests__/` folder following the established patterns\n\nAll should be in `/src/components/generate/` with tests in `/src/components/generate/__tests__/`"}],"totalDurationMs":44130,"totalTokens":125390,"totalToolUseCount":21,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":457,"cache_read_input_tokens":121848,"output_tokens":3079,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":457},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":6,"output_tokens":3079,"cache_read_input_tokens":121848,"cache_creation_input_tokens":457,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":457,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"toolStats":{"readCount":14,"searchCount":3,"bashCount":4,"editFileCount":0,"linesAdded":0,"linesRemoved":0,"otherToolCount":0}}}
