{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Vet9FrRrw3Xg27ZBpgjmKY","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"use client\";\n2\t\n3\timport { useCallback, useState } from \"react\";\n4\t\n5\t// ─── Types ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n6\t\n7\texport interface EventPayload {\n8\t  event_name: string;\n9\t  device_id?: string;\n10\t  user_id?: string;\n11\t  timestamp?: string;\n12\t  properties?: Record<string, unknown>;\n13\t}\n14\t\n15\texport interface SendResult {\n16\t  success: boolean;\n17\t  error?: string;\n18\t}\n19\t\n20\texport interface SeedResult {\n21\t  success: boolean;\n22\t  eventCount?: number;\n23\t  error?: string;\n24\t}\n25\t\n26\texport interface UseEventSenderResult {\n27\t  lastDeviceId: string | null;\n28\t  sendEvent: (payload: EventPayload) => Promise<SendResult>;\n29\t  sendSeed: () => Promise<SeedResult>;\n30\t  loading: boolean;\n31\t}\n32\t\n33\t// ─── Helpers ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n34\t\n35\texport function generateId(): string {\n36\t  return Math.random().toString(36).slice(2, 10);\n37\t}\n38\t\n39\t// ─── Hook ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n40\t\n41\texport function useEventSender(): UseEventSenderResult {\n42\t  const [lastDeviceId, setLastDeviceId] = useState<string | null>(null);\n43\t  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);\n44\t\n45\t  const sendEvent = useCallback(\n46\t    async (payload: EventPayload): Promise<SendResult> => {\n47\t      setLoading(true);\n48\t      try {\n49\t        const res = await fetch(\"/api/events\", {\n50\t          method: \"POST\",\n51\t          headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n52\t          body: JSON.stringify(payload),\n53\t        });\n54\t\n55\t        if (!res.ok) {\n56\t          const data = (await res.json()) as { error?: string };\n57\t          return {\n58\t            success: false,\n59\t            error: data.error ?? `HTTP ${res.status}`,\n60\t          };\n61\t        }\n62\t\n63\t        if (payload.device_id) {\n64\t          setLastDeviceId(payload.device_id);\n65\t        }\n66\t\n67\t        return { success: true };\n68\t      } catch (err) {\n69\t        return {\n70\t          success: false,\n71\t          error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : \"Unknown error\",\n72\t        };\n73\t      } finally {\n74\t        setLoading(false);\n75\t      }\n76\t    },\n77\t    [],\n78\t  );\n79\t\n80\t  const sendSeed = useCallback(async (): Promise<SeedResult> => {\n81\t    setLoading(true);\n82\t    try {\n83\t      const res = await fetch(\"/api/seed\", { method: \"POST\" });\n84\t\n85\t      if (!res.ok) {\n86\t        const data = (await res.json()) as { error?: string };\n87\t        return {\n88\t          success: false,\n89\t          error: data.error ?? `HTTP ${res.status}`,\n90\t        };\n91\t      }\n92\t\n93\t      const statusRes = await fetch(\"/api/seed/status\");\n94\t      const statusData = (await statusRes.json()) as {\n95\t        event_count?: number;\n96\t        user_count?: number;\n97\t      };\n98\t\n99\t      return { success: true, eventCount: statusData.event_count };\n100\t    } catch (err) {\n101\t      return {\n102\t        success: false,\n103\t        error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : \"Unknown error\",\n104\t      };\n105\t    } finally {\n106\t      setLoading(false);\n107\t    }\n108\t  }, []);\n109\t\n110\t  return { lastDeviceId, sendEvent, sendSeed, loading };\n111\t}\n112\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e2b9e14-c306-4c04-b64f-1d0d531c58b6","uuid":"3bea75ec-f201-4b48-ac5b-a5b4d1b58815","timestamp":"2026-04-15T18:40:06.394Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/components/test/useEventSender.ts","content":"\"use client\";\n\nimport { useCallback, useState } from \"react\";\n\n// ─── Types ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport interface EventPayload {\n  event_name: string;\n  device_id?: string;\n  user_id?: string;\n  timestamp?: string;\n  properties?: Record<string, unknown>;\n}\n\nexport interface SendResult {\n  success: boolean;\n  error?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface SeedResult {\n  success: boolean;\n  eventCount?: number;\n  error?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface UseEventSenderResult {\n  lastDeviceId: string | null;\n  sendEvent: (payload: EventPayload) => Promise<SendResult>;\n  sendSeed: () => Promise<SeedResult>;\n  loading: boolean;\n}\n\n// ─── Helpers ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport function generateId(): string {\n  return Math.random().toString(36).slice(2, 10);\n}\n\n// ─── Hook ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport function useEventSender(): UseEventSenderResult {\n  const [lastDeviceId, setLastDeviceId] = useState<string | null>(null);\n  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);\n\n  const sendEvent = useCallback(\n    async (payload: EventPayload): Promise<SendResult> => {\n      setLoading(true);\n      try {\n        const res = await fetch(\"/api/events\", {\n          method: \"POST\",\n          headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n          body: JSON.stringify(payload),\n        });\n\n        if (!res.ok) {\n          const data = (await res.json()) as { error?: string };\n          return {\n            success: false,\n            error: data.error ?? `HTTP ${res.status}`,\n          };\n        }\n\n        if (payload.device_id) {\n          setLastDeviceId(payload.device_id);\n        }\n\n        return { success: true };\n      } catch (err) {\n        return {\n          success: false,\n          error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : \"Unknown error\",\n        };\n      } finally {\n        setLoading(false);\n      }\n    },\n    [],\n  );\n\n  const sendSeed = useCallback(async (): Promise<SeedResult> => {\n    setLoading(true);\n    try {\n      const res = await fetch(\"/api/seed\", { method: \"POST\" });\n\n      if (!res.ok) {\n        const data = (await res.json()) as { error?: string };\n        return {\n          success: false,\n          error: data.error ?? `HTTP ${res.status}`,\n        };\n      }\n\n      const statusRes = await fetch(\"/api/seed/status\");\n      const statusData = (await statusRes.json()) as {\n        event_count?: number;\n        user_count?: number;\n      };\n\n      return { success: true, eventCount: statusData.event_count };\n    } catch (err) {\n      return {\n        success: false,\n        error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : \"Unknown error\",\n      };\n    } finally {\n      setLoading(false);\n    }\n  }, []);\n\n  return { lastDeviceId, sendEvent, sendSeed, loading };\n}\n","numLines":112,"startLine":1,"totalLines":112}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01U2PwRLRWE8BRrR1iVVGM25","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the code patterns. Let me plan my implementation:\n\n1. First, I'll write the unit tests (Step 1 per the sprint plan)\n2. Then implement the production code\n\nThe plan calls for:\n- `src/components/generate/useGenerator.ts` — hook\n- `src/components/generate/GeneratorForm.tsx` — config form\n- `src/components/generate/ProgressPanel.tsx` — progress panel\n- `src/components/generate/JobList.tsx` — job list\n- Tests in `src/components/generate/__tests__/`\n- Modify `src/app/generate/page.tsx`\n\n\n- The useGenerator hook will handle form state with sensible defaults (10,000 total events, 100 users, 30-day window), manage preset templates, and coordinate with the API through startJob and cancelJob methods that handle SSE connections for real-time status updates.\n- For testing in jsdom, I'll need to mock EventSource since it's not available in that environment.\n- The test suite will verify the initial state matches the spec, that each preset correctly updates the form values, and that startJob makes the right API call with the form data.\n- I'm also checking that the job lifecycle works correctly—when a job starts, it opens an SSE connection to track progress, updates state as messages arrive, and properly closes when the job completes or fails.\n- The cancel endpoint gets called when the user stops a job, error handling works when the initial POST fails, and toggling identity resolution resets the anonymous ratio.\n- For the form component tests, I'm verifying all the inputs render, the preset buttons are present and labeled correctly, and clicking them triggers the right callbacks.\n- The submit button should only be clickable when a job isn't running, and the anonymous slider should be disabled when identity resolution is turned off.\n- For the progress panel, I need to check that the progress bar shows the right percentage, throughput and ETA display correctly, and the cancel button only appears while the job is running.\n- When the job completes, I should show links to the explore and trends pages instead of the cancel button.\n- Now I'm setting up the test infrastructure—I'll need to mock fetch and EventSource globally to test the hook behavior, then define the form state interface that tracks all the inputs.\n- The progress state will track the job ID, status, insertion count, throughput, and ETA, while the hook result combines everything together with methods to start, cancel, and fetch jobs.\n- Writing the hook implementation and tests... Still writing the hook implementation... I need to handle a special case where toggling `identity_resolution` off should reset `anonymous_ratio` to 0, so I'll build that logic into the `setForm` function. Now I'm planning out the file structure with the hook, form component, progress panel, job list, and their corresponding tests, then I'll implement them all.\n\nFor the tests, I need to configure the environment properly—the hook test will need jsdom since it uses EventSource, similar to how the existing useTrends test is set up.\n\nSince there's no existing test for useLiveFeed, I'll need to mock EventSource for testing the SSE functionality. Setting up a mock EventSource class...\n\nWriting test files... Setting up test mocks and helper functions...\n\nActually, I should reconsider how I'm structuring this hook.\n\nI need to define the hook interface first before writing tests—it should expose form state management, preset application, job control methods, and track progress through properties like `jobActive`, `progress`, and `jobs`. For the test plan, I'm thinking about how `startJob()` should set `jobActive` to true and establish an SSE connection, so I can verify that calling it creates an EventSource instance and updates the state accordingly.\n\nI also need to handle the case where toggling `identity_resolution` off automatically resets `anonymous_ratio` to 0—that's a dependent state update I'll need to implement in the hook. Now I'm ready to write the test files and production code together, starting with the component tests that define what props `GeneratorForm` and `ProgressPanel` should accept. I need to verify that the SSE connection opens to the correct endpoint and that `jobActive` transitions properly—it should be true after the POST succeeds and the EventSource connects, then flip to false when a terminal message arrives. I'm going to write the test files now, making sure to use the jsdom environment for the hook tests since they use `renderHook` from React Testing Library.\n\nFor the hook's EventSource cleanup, I need to ensure it closes both when the component unmounts and when a terminal status is received. I also need to handle the `identity_resolution` toggle logic in `setForm`—when that flag is toggled off, it should reset `anonymous_ratio` to 0.\n\nWriting the form state update logic...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2324,"cache_read_input_tokens":49702,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2324},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e2b9e14-c306-4c04-b64f-1d0d531c58b6","uuid":"147c8ecb-0fd9-4ad3-bbe0-5fbd314f7125"}
