{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LAs1nFdDnYWEzpHgdT7Vyz","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"use client\";\n2\t\n3\timport Box from \"@mui/material/Box\";\n4\timport Chip from \"@mui/material/Chip\";\n5\timport Stack from \"@mui/material/Stack\";\n6\timport TextField from \"@mui/material/TextField\";\n7\timport Typography from \"@mui/material/Typography\";\n8\t\n9\t// ─── Types ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n10\t\n11\tinterface FunnelDateRangeProps {\n12\t  startDate: string;\n13\t  endDate: string;\n14\t  onStartDateChange: (v: string) => void;\n15\t  onEndDateChange: (v: string) => void;\n16\t}\n17\t\n18\t// ─── Helpers ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n19\t\n20\tfunction todayISO(): string {\n21\t  return new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10);\n22\t}\n23\t\n24\tfunction daysAgoISO(days: number): string {\n25\t  const d = new Date();\n26\t  d.setDate(d.getDate() - days);\n27\t  return d.toISOString().slice(0, 10);\n28\t}\n29\t\n30\t// ─── Component ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n31\t\n32\texport function FunnelDateRange({\n33\t  startDate,\n34\t  endDate,\n35\t  onStartDateChange,\n36\t  onEndDateChange,\n37\t}: FunnelDateRangeProps): React.JSX.Element {\n38\t  function handlePreset(days: number) {\n39\t    onStartDateChange(daysAgoISO(days));\n40\t    onEndDateChange(todayISO());\n41\t  }\n42\t\n43\t  return (\n44\t    <Box data-testid=\"funnel-date-range\">\n45\t      <Typography variant=\"caption\" color=\"text.secondary\" gutterBottom>\n46\t        Date range\n47\t      </Typography>\n48\t      <Stack direction=\"row\" spacing={1} sx={{ mb: 1 }}>\n49\t        <Chip\n50\t          label=\"Last 7d\"\n51\t          size=\"small\"\n52\t          clickable\n53\t          onClick={() => handlePreset(7)}\n54\t        />\n55\t        <Chip\n56\t          label=\"Last 30d\"\n57\t          size=\"small\"\n58\t          clickable\n59\t          onClick={() => handlePreset(30)}\n60\t        />\n61\t        <Chip\n62\t          label=\"Last 90d\"\n63\t          size=\"small\"\n64\t          clickable\n65\t          onClick={() => handlePreset(90)}\n66\t        />\n67\t      </Stack>\n68\t      <Box sx={{ display: \"flex\", gap: 1 }}>\n69\t        <TextField\n70\t          label=\"Start\"\n71\t          type=\"date\"\n72\t          size=\"small\"\n73\t          value={startDate}\n74\t          onChange={(e) => onStartDateChange(e.target.value)}\n75\t          slotProps={{ inputLabel: { shrink: true } }}\n76\t        />\n77\t        <TextField\n78\t          label=\"End\"\n79\t          type=\"date\"\n80\t          size=\"small\"\n81\t          value={endDate}\n82\t          onChange={(e) => onEndDateChange(e.target.value)}\n83\t          slotProps={{ inputLabel: { shrink: true } }}\n84\t        />\n85\t      </Box>\n86\t    </Box>\n87\t  );\n88\t}\n89\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e2b9e14-c306-4c04-b64f-1d0d531c58b6","uuid":"7794b2b3-5c6c-49d7-948b-3e55e133b64c","timestamp":"2026-04-15T18:41:11.059Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/components/funnels/FunnelDateRange.tsx","content":"\"use client\";\n\nimport Box from \"@mui/material/Box\";\nimport Chip from \"@mui/material/Chip\";\nimport Stack from \"@mui/material/Stack\";\nimport TextField from \"@mui/material/TextField\";\nimport Typography from \"@mui/material/Typography\";\n\n// ─── Types ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\ninterface FunnelDateRangeProps {\n  startDate: string;\n  endDate: string;\n  onStartDateChange: (v: string) => void;\n  onEndDateChange: (v: string) => void;\n}\n\n// ─── Helpers ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunction todayISO(): string {\n  return new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10);\n}\n\nfunction daysAgoISO(days: number): string {\n  const d = new Date();\n  d.setDate(d.getDate() - days);\n  return d.toISOString().slice(0, 10);\n}\n\n// ─── Component ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport function FunnelDateRange({\n  startDate,\n  endDate,\n  onStartDateChange,\n  onEndDateChange,\n}: FunnelDateRangeProps): React.JSX.Element {\n  function handlePreset(days: number) {\n    onStartDateChange(daysAgoISO(days));\n    onEndDateChange(todayISO());\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <Box data-testid=\"funnel-date-range\">\n      <Typography variant=\"caption\" color=\"text.secondary\" gutterBottom>\n        Date range\n      </Typography>\n      <Stack direction=\"row\" spacing={1} sx={{ mb: 1 }}>\n        <Chip\n          label=\"Last 7d\"\n          size=\"small\"\n          clickable\n          onClick={() => handlePreset(7)}\n        />\n        <Chip\n          label=\"Last 30d\"\n          size=\"small\"\n          clickable\n          onClick={() => handlePreset(30)}\n        />\n        <Chip\n          label=\"Last 90d\"\n          size=\"small\"\n          clickable\n          onClick={() => handlePreset(90)}\n        />\n      </Stack>\n      <Box sx={{ display: \"flex\", gap: 1 }}>\n        <TextField\n          label=\"Start\"\n          type=\"date\"\n          size=\"small\"\n          value={startDate}\n          onChange={(e) => onStartDateChange(e.target.value)}\n          slotProps={{ inputLabel: { shrink: true } }}\n        />\n        <TextField\n          label=\"End\"\n          type=\"date\"\n          size=\"small\"\n          value={endDate}\n          onChange={(e) => onEndDateChange(e.target.value)}\n          slotProps={{ inputLabel: { shrink: true } }}\n        />\n      </Box>\n    </Box>\n  );\n}\n","numLines":89,"startLine":1,"totalLines":89}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01GP65JnB3D8jUUjCJGQdnxJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. I see that MUI TextField is used for date inputs. Now let me start writing the files.\n\nI'll start with the test files first, then the production code. Let me think through the API carefully.\n\nFor the useGenerator hook:\n- `form`: GeneratorFormState\n- `setForm(updates: Partial<GeneratorFormState>)`: with special logic for identity_resolution toggle\n- `applyPreset(preset)`: applies preset values to form\n- `startJob()`: calls POST /api/generate/start, opens SSE, returns error or void\n\n\n- `cancelJob()`: calls POST /api/generate/[job_id]/cancel\n- `fetchJobs()`: calls GET /api/generate/jobs\n- `jobActive`: boolean\n- `progress`: ProgressState (null initially, populated when job is running)\n- `jobs`: JobState[]\n- `error`: string | null\n\nI need to handle the identity_resolution toggle carefully—when it's disabled, anonymous_ratio should reset to 0. Now I'm thinking about how to test the SSE connection, which means I'll need to mock EventSource since jsdom doesn't include it natively.\n\nFor the startJob test, I'll mock fetch to return a job ID, stub EventSource, then verify that jobActive becomes true and EventSource connects to the right status endpoint. For progress updates, I'll simulate SSE messages and check that the progress state changes accordingly. And when a terminal status message arrives, jobActive should flip back to false.\n\nWriting the test cases...\n\nNow I'm defining the component prop interfaces—GeneratorForm takes the form state and handlers, ProgressPanel needs the progress data and a cancel callback, and JobList just displays the job array. I'm also mapping out the date ranges for the preset scenarios, where realistic covers the last month, high-volume extends to three months, and stress-test will span even longer.\n\nThe test expectations are clear: each preset applies specific load parameters and date ranges, so I need to make sure those values align across the test cases and implementation. I'm going to write out all the necessary files in order—starting with the tests, then the hooks and components, and finally updating the main page. I need to make sure the hook captures an error state when the initial POST request fails, and I'm looking at what the default event types should be in the form based on the generator configuration.\n\nNow I'm implementing the useGenerator hook with the POST to start the job, setting up the EventSource connection to stream status updates, and handling cleanup when the component unmounts.\n\nWriting the hook implementation... Writing test assertions... Writing test cases...\n\nNow I'm thinking through the error handling for `startJob()` — when the POST request fails, I need to make sure the error state gets populated rather than just silently failing.\n\nWriting test files... Writing the test suite...\n\nNow I'm moving on to build the ProgressPanel component, which will display the job progress, status updates, and allow users to cancel running jobs.\n\nFor the GeneratorForm, I need to construct several input sections: numeric fields for event counts and user totals, date pickers for the time range, checkboxes paired with weight sliders for each event type to control their distribution, a toggle for identity resolution that conditionally enables an anonymous ratio slider, a variance level selector, preset configuration buttons, and the main generate action button.\n\nThe event mix section is the trickiest part—each event type needs both a checkbox to include or exclude it and an associated slider to weight its frequency relative to the others.\n\nFor testing, I'm planning to verify all these form elements render correctly by querying for spinbuttons (the number inputs), date inputs, event type checkboxes, the identity resolution switch, and the sliders using their appropriate accessibility roles. I need to figure out the right approach for testing these form elements. Looking at the test requirements, I should verify that all fields render correctly and that the anonymous ratio slider disables when identity resolution is off. Let me stick with role-based queries since that's what the existing tests use, rather than adding data-testid attributes everywhere.\n\nNow I'm defining the TypeScript interfaces for the component props—GeneratorForm needs to accept the form state, a setter function, preset handlers, and submission logic, while ProgressPanel just needs the progress state and a cancel callback.\n\nDefining the component interfaces... I need to decide whether `fetchJobs()` should run automatically when the hook mounts or be called manually—I'll make it auto-run on mount but also expose it for manual refreshes. For the form defaults, I'm computing the date range relative to today, so \"last 30 days\" means the start date is 30 days ago and the end is today. I need to be careful with the date assertions in the tests to account for this relative calculation.\n\nLooking at the existing date utility functions, they use UTC-based ISO strings, which means `new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10)` returns the UTC date rather than the local date—this could differ depending on timezone. I'll mirror that same logic in my tests to compute the expected dates consistently with the implementation.\n\nWriting the test file now...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1732,"cache_read_input_tokens":57238,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1732},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e2b9e14-c306-4c04-b64f-1d0d531c58b6","uuid":"bd3e518d-b43c-4b1f-97bf-3410aece910a"}
