{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013H6KqfeWG6GJiAxaG5Rut3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"MUI v9 Switch renders with `role=\"switch\"`, not `role=\"checkbox\"`. So the test has a factual error - it's querying for `role=\"checkbox\"` but the Switch renders as `role=\"switch\"`.\n\nI need to fix the test to use `role=\"switch\"` instead of `role=\"checkbox\"`. This is a clear factual error.\n\nAlso, I should check whether `inputProps` or `slotProps.input` is the right API for passing aria-label to the Switch in MUI v9.\n\nLet me also check the accessible name for the Switch with role=\"switch\". \n\nThe testing-library query `getByRole(\"switch\", { name: /identity.?resolution/i })` should locate it correctly. But there's a separate issue in another test that uses `getAllByRole(\"checkbox\")` expecting at least 6 checkboxes - if the Switch now has role=\"switch\" instead, that count will be off by one.\n\nNow I'm wondering whether MUI's Checkbox component in v9 also renders with role=\"switch\" or if it still uses the implicit role=\"checkbox\" from the underlying input element.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8241,"cache_read_input_tokens":90572,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8241},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e2b9e14-c306-4c04-b64f-1d0d531c58b6","uuid":"b95f9d9b-f754-4a86-ab2e-409d45ded677"}
