{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01P1TYKbCn4JbBw4ijD5JMMe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The Switch renders as role=\"checkbox\" (via `<input type=\"checkbox\">`), NOT as role=\"switch\". My earlier grep of the Switch.js found `role: 'switch'` but that must be applied elsewhere, not on the input element. The actual input is `<input type=\"checkbox\" aria-label=\"Identity resolution\">` with no explicit role attribute.\n\nSo:\n- The Switch renders as role=\"checkbox\" ✓\n- The aria-label IS correctly set to \"Identity resolution\" ✓ (via slotProps.input)\n\n\n- The accessible name should be \"Identity resolution\"\n\nBut the test is still failing! So why is `getByRole(\"checkbox\", { name: /identity.?resolution/i })` not finding it? I think the `role: 'switch'` I found earlier is actually applied to a parent span element, not the input itself. That means the Switch structure has the role on a wrapper, while the input element inside has type=\"checkbox\" but no explicit role attribute.\n\nWhen testing-library queries for `getByRole(\"checkbox\")`, it should find the input element since it has type=\"checkbox\". The name filter should also work since the input has `aria-label=\"Identity resolution\"`. But the test keeps failing, which is strange. Looking at the debug output, the aria-label is definitely there on the input element, so the query should match...\n\nMaybe in the full form context there's an ID collision or something else interfering with how the accessible name is being computed for that particular FormControlLabel with the Switch input.\n\nActually, looking back at the failing test - I changed it to look for `role=\"switch\"` but the Switch component actually renders with an implicit `role=\"checkbox\"`. That's the mismatch. I need to revert the test back to checking for `role=\"checkbox\"`, but that makes me wonder why the original test was failing in the first place.\n\nThe Switch is wrapped in a FormControlLabel in the GeneratorForm, which should give it the accessible name \"Identity resolution\" through the label prop. My isolated test with the same structure worked fine, so something about the full form context must be interfering.\n\nLooking back at the original test failure, it was searching for a checkbox with that name and failing, even though the Switch should render as `<input type=\"checkbox\">` with the proper aria-label. I switched the query to \"switch\" but that won't work either since the underlying element is a checkbox. The real question is why the original query isn't finding the element when my debug test shows it should be there—possibly the difference between using `slotProps.input` versus the deprecated `inputProps`, though I already updated the component to use the newer API.\n\nLet me revert the test back to searching for \"checkbox\" and run the GeneratorForm test to see if it passes now that the component is properly configured.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":426,"cache_read_input_tokens":103497,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":426},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e2b9e14-c306-4c04-b64f-1d0d531c58b6","uuid":"fdfb1687-c217-427c-a7f7-1dee2ffad613"}
